The paper discusses the modeling and control of microgrids, which involves the application of advanced techniques from control engineering, power systems, and electrical engineering. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which covers topics related to the modeling, analysis, and control of complex systems. The paper also deals with the integration of renewable energy sources, which falls under the category of cs.ET (Energy and Power Systems). Additionally, the paper discusses the physical phenomena behind microgrids, which could be related to cs.PF (Physics and Society) or cs.CE (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper deals with electrical systems and networks, which could be related to cs.EM (Electromagnetics).
